MBA 662: Management of Information Technology. 3 credits.
The strategic, economic and managerial aspects of managing an organization's IT assets are covered. The business value of IT is understood and assessed in context of its impact on the organization's structure and strategy. The course includes discussion on major issues pertaining management of IT infrastructure.Offered by SBUS Multidisciplinary. May not be repeated for credit.
